Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
3 Stars
Less comfortable as seamless compression stockings
I purchased a set of these zippered compression stockings to try as the reviews said they were easier to remove than the standard seamless compression stockings with no zipper. The stockings are well made, and I ordered size L/XL per the sizing chart. I am a women's shoe size 9W and have wide calves. In Solimo brand stockings I wear a size L; in Jobst XL.I have third space edema and experience swelling in my feet and calves sometimes. My physician recommended 8-15mm or 15-20mm compression stockings to control the swelling.This morning it was more difficult to put on this pair of zippered stockings than rolling on a standard pair, and that was before my calf swelled. They became increasingly uncomfortable as the day went on, with the zipper pressing into my calf.As you can see from the photo, there is a deep impression of the zipper along my calf, and the top portion of the zipper scratched the underside of my knee, leaving a small wound that has stabbed over. I was able to remove one of the stockings on my own, and that part was easier than rolling off a standard compression stockings at 15-20mm.The second stockings required assistance from a family member to remove. The zipper had caught on the inside seam.If you are on the smaller end of the size range and do not have problems with edema, these may work great for you. They didn't work well for me and are not going to join my rotation of compression stockings.
